{
  "name": "RPlog_Battle_of_Bothawui_III_25_ABY",
  "title": "Battle of Bothawui III (25 ABY)",
  "summary": "With Drev'starn city fallen to the Republic, the Imperial battle squadron withdraws, its Star Destroyers carrying troops meant to crush the offensive, while Commander Argon Brand -- now aboard the assault frigate Derlin -- moves to see what the Imperials intend. Captain Harval Shaw, commanding the Victory-class Executioner, turns to engage with three Carrack cruisers as Argon doggedly maneuvers to keep the Derlin on the Star Destroyer's port side and away from its forward guns. Through a prolonged duel of turbolasers and ion cannons, Shaw cannot divine the Republic captain's single-minded tactic until, too late, the Derlin makes a reckless head-on overshoot, clearing the Executioner at point-blank range and settling behind its exposed, stabilizer-crippled stern. Argon's broadsides knock out the Executioner's engines, leaving it dead in space, and he demands its surrender. Shaw stalls for time to attempt a hyperspace jump while insisting on speaking to a senior officer, but Captain Cen of the Deliverance orders Argon to fire; the jump fails, two engineers die containing a reactor breach, and Shaw finally yields his ship and crew. As terms are arranged, Shaw quietly marches off to purge his computer core.",
